body: Hey @BenMorel, can you reproduce the issue on https://psalm.dev ?

With `--debug-by-line`:

```
...
Have populated RecursiveIterator
Have populated UnderflowException
Have populated OutOfRangeException
ClassLikeStorage is populated
FileStorage is populating
FileStorage is populated
Finished registering stub files
Analyzing files...
Getting /home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml
Analyzing /home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:1
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:2
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:8
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:10
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:11
/home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/src/View/ActivityView.phtml:11
Uncaught InvalidArgumentException: Could not get class storage for example\view\activityview in /home/benjamin/Projects/example.com/vendor/vimeo/psalm/src/Psalm/Internal/Provider/ClassLikeStorageProvider.php:42
Stack trace:
...
```

ActivityView.phtml:11 is the last line here:

```php
<div class="activities">
    <?php foreach ($this->activities as $activity): ?>
        <?php $showCommentFormByDefault = $this->showCommentFormByDefault($activity); ?>
```

This issue occurs in 3.18.2 as well and did not in 3.17.2 (haven't tested 3.18.0)

Although it may be the same exception from a different  path... I'll report a separate issue.
@BenMorel how does Psalm know what `$this` is in the template?
if it's via `@psalm-scope-this`, I see what the bug is

@muglug It's via `@var`. First two lines of the view script:

```php
<?php declare(strict_types=1); ?>
<?php /** @var Example\View\ActivityView $this */ ?>
```
never mind, the issue is that Psalm doesn't currently expect `@var` types to be set like that (in self-enclosed PHP blocks).
Thank you! Looking forward to the next release :+1:
